        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>This pale wooden wand is carved to resemble a thigh bone with metal caps at each end. Ghostly tendrils seem to swirl around it every so often.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Cast a Spell]{Cast a Spell};</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day, plus overcharge;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You cast @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.False Life]{False Life} at 7th level. During the duration of the spell, wisps that resemble spirits flit around you as long as you have any temporary Hit Points from false life, and you can use the following action.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activation</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">F</span> envision;</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You successfully impart the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened} 1 condition to a creature;</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You have temporary Hit Points;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You end false life and increase the creature's frightened condition value to 2.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> Supply a casting of False Life at 7th level</p>"
